# self-healing protocol — ${NAME}

This plugin uses the same self-healing pattern as `web-tools` (see
`web-tools-plugin/docs/self-healing.md` in the synaps-skills monorepo
for the full reference).

## The contract

Every script does:

1. **PRE** — query memory for relevant prior fixes:
   ```bash
   source lib/memory.sh
   memory_recall "$ERR_TEXT" --tag "domain-$HOST" --tag "op-$OP"
   ```

2. **ACT** — do the real work.

3. **POST** — on failure, log a structured record:
   ```bash
   memory_log_failure "$(jq -nc \
     --arg host "$HOST" --arg op "$OP" --arg cls "$ERR_CLASS" \
     '{host:$host, op:$op, err_class:$cls, exit:1}')"
   ```

   On success, exit 0 (no auto-write — agent decides what to commit).

## Tag conventions

Hyphenated, lowercase:

- `kind-fix` — a verified fix
- `kind-runbook` — a procedure
- `kind-caveat` — a known gotcha
- `domain-<host-with-dashes>` (e.g. `domain-github-com`)
- `op-<operation>` (e.g. `op-fetch`, `op-search`)
- `err-<class>` (e.g. `err-http_403`, `err-timeout`)

## Storage

```
~/.synaps-cli/memory/${NAME}/
  notes/          markdown source of truth
  db/             VelociRAG index (derived, rebuildable)
  failures.jsonl  raw failure log (append-only)
```

`notes/` is the source of truth — `db/` is rebuilt from it via
`velocirag index`.
